-- Cairn, Cipla, Mahindra, Gammon, Binani, Tata Motors: India Equity Preview
-- Pooja Thakur
-- 2010-06-16T03:07:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/cairn-cipla-gammon-infrastructure-and-tata-motors-india-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in India  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the  last close .  
 The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or  Sensex ,
gained 74.66, or 0.4 percent, to 17,412.83, the S&P CNX  Nifty 
Index on the National Stock Exchange rose 0.5 percent to
5,222.35 and the  BSE 200 Index  increased 0.5 percent to 2,205.50.
SGX CNX Nifty Index futures for June delivery rose 0.5 to
5,250.0 at 10:59 a.m. in Singapore.  
 Cairn India Ltd.  (CAIR IN): The operator of India’s biggest
oilfield on land began selling crude oil from its field in
Rajasthan state through a heated pipeline, helping the company
cut transportation costs. The stock added 0.1 percent to 305.25
rupees.  
 Cipla Ltd.  (CIPLA IN): The drugmaker plans to spend $65
million to buy stakes in two biotech companies, it said in a
statement to the Bombay Stock Exchange. Cipla fell 0.7 percent
to 338 rupees.  
 Gammon Infrastructure Projects Ltd.  (GISP IN): The
construction company signed an agreement to buy a company that
is setting up a 250 megawatt coal-based power plant in Western
India, according to a statement to the Bombay Stock Exchange.
The shares rose 0.8 percent to 26.15 rupees.  
 JK Lakshmi Cement Ltd.  (JKLC IN): The maker of the
construction material plans to invest 1 billion rupees ($21.5
million) to set up ready-mix concrete units, the Economic Times
reported, citing a  Shailendra Chouksey , a company executive. The
stock fell 0.6 percent to 62.95 rupees.  
 Tata Motors Ltd.  (TTMT IN): India’s largest truckmaker’s
global sales, including Jaguar and Land Rover vehicles, gained
50 percent in May to 79,819 units, the company said in an e-
mailed statement. The shares slid 0.1 percent to 759.70 rupees.  
